          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A point is contained within the path of a graphics context if the point is inside the painted region when the path is stroked or filled with opaque colors using the specified path drawing mode. A point can be inside a path only if the path is explicitly closed by calling the function ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgcontext/1454508-closepath",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " for paths drawn directly to the current context, or ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgmutablepath/1411188-closesubpath",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " for paths first created as ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgpath",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " objects and then drawn to the current context.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
